PrecisAuthority to enter into a "SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT" with the BLACKFOOT INDIAN BAND (commonly referred to as the SIKSIKA NATION) whose purpose is to resolve a specific claim pertaining to the expropriation and sale to the Canadian Pacific Railway Company, in the year 1910, of some 2,336 acres of Blackfoot Indian Reserve No. 146, in the Province of Alberta, for an irrigation dam and flood plain (Horseshoe Dam, now known as Bassano Dam).
